					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12889917#post-4458436</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12889917/scp-4432#post-4458436</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 31 Dec 2019 18:35:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lt Flops</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1735419</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm a bit iffy on this one. The ending, as McB highlighted above, is a <em>powerful</em> gut punch. There is also some good fridge horror in the following line:</p> <div style="display: block; margin: auto; align: center; border: dashed 1px #444; background: #f4f4f4; width: 50%; padding: 10px;"> <p><span style="color: red">youre saying you can make me one of those fancy dolls?</span><br /></p> <div style="text-align: right;"> <p><span style="color: green">dado can make u toy yes</span></p> </div> </div> <p>And the actual &quot;mr mister® by dado&quot; feels exactly like something he would create &#8212; from the dado body horror wackiness, to the showcasing of a typical dado double-meaning. I just can't see why Ricardo would respond to <em>that</em> particular ad, though. I can see him being desperate, but it doesn't even seem adjacent to what he was looking for. While this is definitely one of the more thoughtful dado stories I've read, I personally don't find that the dado and father aspects (which are each great on their own!) mesh together well.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
